cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper focuses on natural language processing tasks such as spatial role labeling and word embeddings, which are relevant to this sub-category.
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper uses the Microsoft COCO data set to train a deep neural model for forecasting spatial arrangements between visual objects, which is a computer vision task.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses deep learning techniques to improve the performance of spatial role labeling algorithms, which is a sub-field of artificial intelligence.
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a deep multilayer perceptron (MLP) and Long Short Term Memory (LSTM) network for training the model, which are machine learning techniques.
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper uses a fine-tuning method for MLP to improve the F1 measure in classifying words into spatial roles, which is relevant to information retrieval tasks.
